than enough on our own.

152
00:09:11,052 --> 00:09:13,304
Let's split into two groups.
One will trace the FBI agents,

153
00:09:13,429 --> 00:09:15,723
and the other will investigate
the heart attack victims.

154
00:09:16,057 --> 00:09:19,602
There are only a few people who
had access to info from HQ,

155
00:09:19,685 --> 00:09:23,481
and who were beings investigated
by the FBI in the first five days!

156
00:09:23,564 --> 00:09:24,648
Yeah...

157
00:09:25,566 --> 00:09:27,610
So, does anyone have any questions?

158
00:09:28,861 --> 00:09:31,947
Well then, Ryuzaki,
I have a question.

159
00:09:32,782 --> 00:09:35,743
You said earlier that you hate to lose.

160
00:09:36,243 --> 00:09:38,662
But you've shown us your face.

161
00:09:38,746 --> 00:09:41,123
Doesn't that mean that you've
already lost to Kira?

162
00:09:41,957 --> 00:09:43,167
That's correct.

163
00:09:43,250 --> 00:09:44,960
The fact that I've shown my face

164
00:09:45,086 --> 00:09:48,839
and that I've sacrificed
twelve FBI agents are both <i>losses.</i>

165
00:09:49,632 --> 00:09:51,509
But I will win in the end.

166
00:09:52,301 --> 00:09:54,595
This is the first time
I've laid my life on the line.

167
00:09:55,304 --> 00:09:58,682
Let's show Kira that
we're willing to risk our lives...

168
00:10:00,935 --> 00:10:03,104
Because justice will definitely prevail.

169
00:10:04,271 --> 00:10:05,356
T-That's right...

170
00:10:05,481 --> 00:10:07,024
Justice will prevail!

171
00:10:07,149 --> 00:10:08,192
Let's give it our best!

172
00:10:08,442 --> 00:10:10,361
Let's do this, Ryuzaki!

173
00:10:11,403 --> 00:10:15,324
<i>When I first saw him,
I was suspicious, but...</i>

174
00:10:15,741 --> 00:10:16,784
<i>There's no mistake.</i>

175
00:10:16,992 --> 00:10:18,661
<i>This man is L.</i>

176
00:10:19,161 --> 00:10:22,832
First off, in order to make sure
Kira isn't among us,

177
00:10:23,124 --> 00:10:25,793
I would like to talk to each of
you individually.

178
00:10:26,460 --> 00:10:27,878
Huh? Oh, yeah.

179
00:10:28,629 --> 00:10:30,214
So he doesn't trust us...

180
00:10:30,464 --> 00:10:32,341
It's understandable.

181
00:10:33,134 --> 00:10:36,470
If Kira was in the task force HQ
in the beginning, gathering info...

182
00:10:36,679 --> 00:10:38,889
chances are high that
he's still here.

183
00:10:39,640 --> 00:10:40,683
' Get n!

184
00:10:40,766 --> 00:10:43,477
And if he remained
he's seen Ryuzaki's face.

185
00:10:44,270 --> 00:10:46,063
Even this is a risk, huh?

186
00:10:47,356 --> 00:10:48,816
<i>Things have been going well so far.</i>

187
00:10:49,650 --> 00:10:54,238
<i>If only I had one more thing,
just one more decisive clue...</i>

188
00:10:55,322 --> 00:10:57,408
<i>If there was just one thing I missed...</i>

189
00:10:58,117 --> 00:11:00,578
<i>Just one piece of evidence
that would come to light...</i>

190
00:11:01,829 --> 00:11:03,247
<i>It could cost me my life.</i>

191
00:11:04,165 --> 00:11:05,666
<i>- Just one thing...
- Just one thing...</i>

192
00:11:28,189 --> 00:11:30,107
Did you finish studying?

193
00:11:30,733 --> 00:11:31,775
Yeah.

194
00:11:32,318 --> 00:11:33,277
<i>It's all right.</i>

195
00:11:33,402 --> 00:11:34,528
<i>There wasn't anything I missed.</i>

196
00:11:34,820 --> 00:11:38,282
<i>My biggest gamble was
the bus-jacking incident, but...</i>

197
00:11:39,366 --> 00:11:41,702
<i>It is impossible to
connect it with Kira.</i>

198
00:11:42,870 --> 00:11:44,121
<i>The police and I don't know</i>

199
00:11:44,371 --> 00:11:47,958
<i>that Kira can kill people with
means other than heart attacks.</i>

200
00:11:48,918 --> 00:11:51,754
<i>But if anyone were to
discover that fact,</i>

201
00:11:51,837 --> 00:11:53,881
<i>it would be a huge problem for me.</i>

202
00:11:54,173 --> 00:11:56,425
What? Right now?

203
00:11:56,759 --> 00:11:59,470
Dad's been pulling all nighters.
He needs clean clothes.

204
00:11:59,553 --> 00:12:01,096
You've got to give this to him.

205
00:12:01,222 --> 00:12:04,266
I promised I'd go to the first
New Year's Shrine Visit with my friends!

206
00:12:04,350 --> 00:12:05,309
<i>I'll go.</i>

207
00:12:05,726 --> 00:12:06,810
I could use a break.

208
00:12:06,936 --> 00:12:08,062
How lucky!

209
00:12:08,103 --> 00:12:09,813
Thank you, Light!

210
00:12:10,898 --> 00:12:13,400
That means that you can
spy on the Police Department.

211
00:12:13,859 --> 00:12:15,819
<i>I'll</i> only be able to go as far as
the reception though.

212
00:12:20,783 --> 00:12:22,910
Oh? You're bringing a page?

213
00:12:23,410 --> 00:12:24,787
Killing someone out there?

214
00:12:25,204 --> 00:12:27,748
Lately, I've been doing
this when I go out.

215
00:12:27,957 --> 00:12:28,999
Just in case.

216
00:12:34,088 --> 00:12:35,172
<i>That day...</i>

217
00:12:35,923 --> 00:12:38,509
<i>Raye said that he was going to
go to Shinjuku.</i>

218
00:12:41,428 --> 00:12:42,429
<i>On that same day,</i>

219
00:12:42,471 --> 00:12:45,599
<i>there were four heart attacks
in the Shinjuku area.</i>

220
00:12:46,433 --> 00:12:48,852
<i>And. . .a bus-jacking...</i>

221
00:12:48,852 --> 00:12:49,353
BUS-JACKER DIES AFTER
BEING HIT BY CAR

222
00:12:50,646 --> 00:12:51,855
<i>It's not a coincidence.</i>

223
00:12:52,606 --> 00:12:53,399
<i>Kira can...</i>

224
00:12:57,278 --> 00:12:58,737
NATIONAL POLICE AGENCY AND
NATIONAL PUBLIC SAFETY COMMISSION

225
00:13:01,949 --> 00:13:04,451
<i>kill in ways other than heart attacks.</i>

226
00:13:06,662 --> 00:13:08,163
<i>The number you have just dialed...</i>

227
00:13:08,205 --> 00:13:09,999
That's unusual for Dad...

228
00:13:12,418 --> 00:13:15,129
NATIONAL POLICE AGENCY AND
NATIONAL PUBLIC SAFETY COMMISSION

229
00:13:15,129 --> 00:13:15,379
I wonder if he's at
an important meeting...

230
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:19,008
Please...

231
00:13:19,425 --> 00:13:22,970
I must speak directly to someone
from the task force.

232
00:13:23,679 --> 00:13:25,723
I've told you already,

233
00:13:25,973 --> 00:13:29,018
there is no one in
the Kira Task Force Headquarters.

234
00:13:29,852 --> 00:13:31,312
<i>There's no one at headquarters?</i>

235
00:13:31,937 --> 00:13:34,523
<i>Dad's phone is off...
What's going on?</i>

236
00:13:35,316 --> 00:13:37,026
ls there any way I can contact them?

237
00:13:37,484 --> 00:13:39,987
It's something very important
regarding the Kira investigation.

238
00:13:40,654 --> 00:13:41,822
<i>The Kira investigation?!</i>

239
00:13:44,992 --> 00:13:47,703
Well, I'll try to call their headquarters
once more.

240
00:13:49,163 --> 00:13:52,082
I'm Detective Superintendent
Soichiro Yagami's son, Light.

241
00:13:52,624 --> 00:13:53,834
I brought a change of clothes
for my father,

242
00:13:53,876 --> 00:13:56,253
but it doesn't look like he's here,
could you hold on these for him?

243
00:13:56,712 --> 00:13:58,922
Sure. Light, I haven't seen you
around in a while.

244
00:13:59,048 --> 00:14:01,175
Oh...sorry.
Umm...

245
00:14:01,550 --> 00:14:06,055
Remember? We solved that
insurance murder with your advice.

246
00:14:06,722 --> 00:14:08,515
I was the receptionist then, too.

247
00:14:09,224 --> 00:14:11,101
Really, I'm sorry...

248
00:14:11,685 --> 00:14:13,687
I just write my name here, right?

249
00:14:14,480 --> 00:14:17,608
Does this mean that you're
going to help outwith the Kira case, too?

250
00:14:17,983 --> 00:14:20,861
Yes, if all goes well,
I may be able to beat L.

251
00:14:21,195 --> 00:14:22,780
<i>Beat L?</i>

252
00:14:23,530 --> 00:14:25,741
Nobody's at headquarters.

253
00:14:26,075 --> 00:14:28,035
Please trust me on this.

254
00:14:28,243 --> 00:14:30,204
I'll be sure to give them
your message.

255
00:14:30,704 --> 00:14:31,789
That won't do.

256
00:14:31,872 --> 00:14:33,207
It must be in person.

257
00:14:33,332 --> 00:14:34,416
Excuse me...

258
00:14:35,042 --> 00:14:37,628
My father is the chief leading
the Kira investigation.

259
00:14:38,212 --> 00:14:40,130
Do you want to leave
a message with me?

260
00:14:40,923 --> 00:14:43,926
His cell phone is off,
so I can't tell him immediately.

261
00:14:45,052 --> 00:14:46,720
But they're probably busy.

262
00:14:47,096 --> 00:14:48,430
A bunch of FBI agents were killed,

263
00:14:48,514 --> 00:14:52,226
and a lot of detectives quit the case
because they were afraid of Kira.

264
00:14:52,893 --> 00:14:55,646
Light, you shouldn't be
telling civilians that...

265
00:14:56,397 --> 00:14:59,108
People are already talking about it.

266
00:14:59,775 --> 00:15:01,485
Besides, this person is trustworthy.

267
00:15:01,944 --> 00:15:03,278
I can tell by looking at her eyes.

268
00:15:03,862 --> 00:15:05,489
She's a very wise and careful person.

269
00:15:06,407 --> 00:15:08,909
You've heard about the FBI incident,
and you figured out that

270
00:15:08,951 --> 00:15:11,328
there's a problem within
the Japanese police force itself.

271
00:15:11,912 --> 00:15:15,624
That's why you want to speak
directly to headquarters.

272
00:15:16,458 --> 00:15:17,459
Did I get that right?

273
00:15:21,130 --> 00:15:22,798
I'll probably get a call
from my father

274
00:15:23,132 --> 00:15:25,092
once he gets the message
I left on his phone.

275
00:15:25,759 --> 00:15:28,178
You can talk directly
to him at that time.

276
00:15:28,720 --> 00:15:29,847
Is it all right?

277
00:15:30,264 --> 00:15:31,348
Of course!

278
00:15:31,473 --> 00:15:34,309
I can't give you my father's
cell phone number,

279
00:15:34,601 --> 00:15:37,020
but you can use my phone.

280
00:15:37,312 --> 00:15:41,442
Of course, it's no use if
you don't trust both of us...

281
00:15:43,277 --> 00:15:45,362
<i>Who is this cheery guy?</i>

282
00:15:47,448 --> 00:15:48,490
Thank you.

283
00:15:50,075 --> 00:15:52,536
You've managed to lead
her along well, Light.

284
00:15:54,997 --> 00:15:57,833
You're pretty brave.

285
00:15:58,333 --> 00:16:00,335
To involve yourself in the Kira case.

286
00:16:01,128 --> 00:16:02,212
Not at all...

287
00:16:02,421 --> 00:16:04,339
You think that Kira is...

288
00:16:06,467 --> 00:16:11,847
Um, may I ask what your name is?
My name is Light Yagami.

289
00:16:12,306 --> 00:16:15,476
Light as in the character for "moon,"
and Yagami as in "night god."

290
00:16:16,143 --> 00:16:17,227
It's a strange name, isn't it?

291
00:16:18,479 --> 00:16:19,646
I'm Shoko Maki.

292
00:16:19,980 --> 00:16:21,899
Shoko for "shining child,"

293
00:16:22,024 --> 00:16:24,026
and Maki as in "space" and "tree."

294
00:16:24,276 --> 00:16:25,819
Ms. Maki, right?

295
00:16:28,322 --> 00:16:32,242
Ms. Maki, I think that Kira's powers...

296
00:16:32,826 --> 00:16:36,246
enable him to control
his victims before he kills them.

297
00:16:36,330 --> 00:16:37,748
L-I thought so too. ...!

298
00:16:38,707 --> 00:16:41,084
That's exactly what I was thinking!

299
00:16:41,627 --> 00:16:43,921
Kira can control the actions
of a person before death.

300
00:16:44,171 --> 00:16:45,214
But that's not all...

301
00:16:45,631 --> 00:16:47,257
If my analysis is correct...

302
00:16:48,050 --> 00:16:51,386
Kira can also kill people in
Ways other than heart attacks.

303
00:16:52,638 --> 00:16:55,015
<i>Who is this woman?</i>

304
00:16:56,225 --> 00:16:58,560
I don't think anyone's noticed yet...

305
00:16:59,061 --> 00:17:02,564
But I think this is what's
going to catch Kira.

306
00:17:04,024 --> 00:17:06,360
I hadn't even thought about that.

307
00:17:06,860 --> 00:17:08,362
But if that's the case,

308
00:17:08,403 --> 00:17:10,614
Kira would make sure not to
give his victims heart attacks

309
00:17:10,739 --> 00:17:12,699
when he's intent on hiding a murder.

310
00:17:13,158 --> 00:17:16,745
Yes, someone I know
may have met Kira.

311
00:17:17,079 --> 00:17:18,121
Met Kira?!

312
00:17:20,541 --> 00:17:21,583
Sorry.

313
00:17:21,667 --> 00:17:24,545
Meeting Kira is definitely something

314
00:17:24,586 --> 00:17:26,630
that the police would have
a hard time believing.

315
00:17:26,880 --> 00:17:30,092
Yes, that's why I have to
explain it in detail to

316
00:17:30,175 --> 00:17:32,803
someone from
task force headquarters.

317
00:17:33,011 --> 00:17:36,974
But wouldn't it be better if
that person spoke to them instead?

318
00:17:38,267 --> 00:17:40,435
That person is no longer alive.

319
00:17:41,353 --> 00:17:44,648
He was one of the FBI agents
who came to Japan.

320
00:17:46,567 --> 00:17:49,653
<i>An FBI agent who met Kira...</i>

321
00:17:50,529 --> 00:17:51,572
<i>C-Could it be?</i>

322
00:17:51,738 --> 00:17:53,824
He was also my fiancé.

323
00:17:54,783 --> 00:17:57,578
He said that he witnessed
a bus-jacking incident.

324
00:17:58,120 --> 00:18:01,415
He probably met Kira
on that bus.

325
00:18:02,249 --> 00:18:04,251
<i>Raye Penber!</i>

326
00:18:09,715 --> 00:18:10,757
What's wrong?

327
00:18:11,425 --> 00:18:12,426
Oh, nothing.

328
00:18:12,467 --> 00:18:14,261
I'm sorry your fiancé's passed away.

329
00:18:16,722 --> 00:18:19,600
So. . .what makes you think
he met Kira?

330
00:18:20,976 --> 00:18:23,645
Eight days after the bus-jacking...

331
00:18:25,272 --> 00:18:28,191
He died, along with
the other FBI agents.

332
00:18:29,985 --> 00:18:33,780
That hijacker robbed
a bank two days earlier.

333
00:18:34,823 --> 00:18:36,867
He died in an accident...

334
00:18:37,492 --> 00:18:39,161
an unusual and rare set of events...

335
00:18:40,495 --> 00:18:42,205
I think that Kira set up
the hijacking

336
00:18:42,623 --> 00:18:45,876
to steal information from my fiancé...

337
00:18:46,460 --> 00:18:51,340
in order to kill the FBI agents
who had come to Japan.

338
00:18:51,798 --> 00:18:55,552
The hijacker died in an accident.

339
00:18:56,011 --> 00:19:00,140
In other words, heart attacks aren't
the only way that Kira can kill.

340
00:19:12,027 --> 00:19:15,072
The hijacker didn't die
of a heart attack.

341
00:19:15,822 --> 00:19:19,034
So that's why you think that Kira can
kill by means other than heart attacks?

342
00:19:19,326 --> 00:19:20,327
Yes.

343
00:19:20,661 --> 00:19:23,830
I think that's a bit of a leap...

344
00:19:24,998 --> 00:19:25,999
No, it's not.

345
00:19:26,041 --> 00:19:30,379
I can't help but think that
the hijacker was being controlled by Kira.

346
00:19:31,046 --> 00:19:32,089
Why?

347
00:19:32,673 --> 00:19:34,049
I've been wondering about

348
00:19:34,132 --> 00:19:36,593
the hijacking ever since
my fiancé told me about it.

349
00:19:37,177 --> 00:19:39,513
I asked him about it more
when he was relaxed.

350
00:19:40,681 --> 00:19:44,434
He didn't name any names,
but he did tell me this.

351
00:19:44,643 --> 00:19:45,602
What did he say?

352
00:19:46,019 --> 00:19:49,940
That he reluctantly showed
his FBI ID to someone.

353
00:19:54,903 --> 00:19:56,029
It was a top-secret investigation

354
00:19:56,071 --> 00:19:57,614
that the FBI kept secret from
the Japanese police.

355
00:19:57,906 --> 00:20:00,409
He wasn't supposed to show his ID.

356
00:20:01,201 --> 00:20:06,540
So whoever saw his ID was the one
who let slip that the FBI was in Japan.

357
00:20:07,541 --> 00:20:09,626
<i>She really knows what
she's talking about!</i>

358
00:20:09,751 --> 00:20:13,046
<i>So this would be the "one thing"
that Light was worrying about!</i>

359
00:20:13,547 --> 00:20:14,631
I see.

360
00:20:14,881 --> 00:20:18,385
It's a conclusion you came to
with your singular knowledge

361
00:20:18,427 --> 00:20:20,637
and your desire to avenge your fiance.

362
00:20:21,263 --> 00:20:22,723
You believe that Kira can
murder his victims

363
00:20:22,764 --> 00:20:24,266
by means other than by heart attacks.

364
00:20:24,558 --> 00:20:25,642
Yes.

365
00:20:25,767 --> 00:20:27,060
You have some
amazing deductive skills,

366
00:20:27,102 --> 00:20:28,770
but you can't deny you have
personal interests in this case.

367
00:20:28,854 --> 00:20:30,647
Your argument seems a bit forced.

368
00:20:33,525 --> 00:20:36,486
But. . .this theory is definitely
worth investigating.

369
00:20:37,112 --> 00:20:38,947
Your testimony will be
very important to the case.

370
00:20:39,448 --> 00:20:40,574
Y-Yes.

371
00:20:41,241 --> 00:20:45,662
If what you said is correct,
Kira should be caught soon...

372
00:20:46,413 --> 00:20:47,497
Because...

373
00:20:47,956 --> 00:20:53,128
Kira was the one your fiancé
showed his ID to on that bus.

374
00:20:53,962 --> 00:20:55,088
Yes.

375
00:21:01,219 --> 00:21:02,345
<i>That was close...</i>

376
00:21:03,805 --> 00:21:07,684
<i>If this woman had told the police
all this before she told me...</i>

377
00:21:09,144 --> 00:21:12,981
<i>It seems like a god other
than a Shinigami</i>

378
00:21:14,483 --> 00:21:16,151
<i>is on my side.</i>

379
00:21:23,617 --> 00:21:26,119
TO BE CONTINUED

380
00:21:26,995 --> 00:21:31,917
<i>I dreamed a dream
that no one could see,</i>

381
00:21:32,042 --> 00:21:37,339
<i>I threw away everything
that I didn't need</i>

382
00:21:37,672 --> 00:21:40,884
<i>I'm holding these feelings</i>

383
00:21:40,967 --> 00:21:46,348
<i>That I can't give up in my heart</i>

384
00:21:46,473 --> 00:21:52,729
<i>Even if my feet fall victim
to the shackles of sacrifice</i>

385
00:21:52,813 --> 00:21:57,317
<i>In between reality and my ideal</i>

386
00:21:58,109 --> 00:22:02,989
<i>I can't hold back
the flooding impulses</i>

387
00:22:03,156 --> 00:22:06,785
<i>Because I have a strong desire</i>

388
00:22:06,868 --> 00:22:10,455
<i>To accomplish</i>

389
00:22:11,081 --> 00:22:15,669
<i>[deceit] [fear] [vanity] [melancholy]</i>

390
00:22:15,752 --> 00:22:21,550
<i>I'm not weak enough to believe</i>

391
00:22:21,633 --> 00:22:26,429
<i>Any of these negative perceptions</i>

392
00:22:26,888 --> 00:22:32,227
<i>I'm a trickster
who doesn't know solitude</i>

393
00:22:36,439 --> 00:22:37,899
PREVIEW

394
00:22:38,275 --> 00:22:41,903
I want to see how
this woman dies,

395
00:22:42,487 --> 00:22:44,281
but I can't be caught
following her.

396
00:22:46,116 --> 00:22:48,952
Go on, hurry to your death!

397
00:22:49,744 --> 00:22:51,496
NEXT EPISODE: OVERCAST

